          <div class="col-lg-6 mobirule">
              <h1>
                  Rules:-
              </h1>
              <hr/>
            <div style="fnt">
              <p>1. &nbsp; Board is divided into a 15×15 grid of squares. The tiles must form words that, in <b>crossword fashion</b>, read left to right in rows or downward in columns, and be included in a standard dictionary. </p>
              <p>2. There are <b>100 tiles</b>, each of them are letters and points associated to them. <b>Rare alphabets (like Q or Z) have more(10) points while common alphabets(like A) have low(1) points.</b></p>
              <p>3. In each turn, you can <b>put word on the board</b> such that choosen word is valid and all words that connects choosen word are also valid, you can <b>change your rack</b> or you can <b>skip your turn.</b></p>
              <p>4. For more information, read this <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scrabble_letter_distributions">wikipedia</a></p>
            </div>
          </div>
